        <p>The main thing idea that we wanted to test was: when presented with a progress bar and a specific bundle of content to complete, would users be more likely to engage and consume the content? Would they also trust the content and believe that it‚Äôs relevant to them after answering a series of questions during onboarding? Would they even go through onboarding?</p>

        <h3 class="article__heading">Outcome</h3>

        <p>Because we wanted to give the HBR team as much confidence on a path forward as we could, we decided to do two additional weeks of user testing and iteration with our Sprint prototype. The HBR folks sourced interested HBR subscribers from all over the world as participants for our user testing, and we hit the ground running.</p>

